description:
drh added on 2014-09-29 14:43:53:
If the content of a table is deleted out from under a SELECT statement
during a reverse order ROWID scan, an assertion fault might result.
The following TCL script illustrates the problem:
sqlite3 db :memory:
db function eval eval
proc eval {sql} {db eval $sql; return [db changes];}
db eval {
  CREATE TABLE t1(a INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,b);
  INSERT INTO t1(a,b) VALUES(1,'a'),(2,'b'),(3,'c');
  SELECT a, eval('DELETE FROM t1'), b FROM t1 ORDER BY a DESC;
}
The problem was introduced just prior to version 3.8.0 by check-in
[dc65ad8c4c67b21e].  This problem was discovered during internal testing
and analysis and has not been observed in the wild.
